name: Pack Up Your Troubles in Your Old Kit Bag and Smile, Smile, Smile!
comments: Brothers Felix and George Powell wrote and entered this song in a competition. After they won first prize for best marching song , they decided to include it in the repertoire of their entertainment troupe, "The Harlequinaders." This group performed at the London  Hippodrome and other major theaters in Britain. It was first publicly performed in August or early September 1915.
